	<p>Hi, I'm Jamie Terrell.</p>

	<p>
		I've been fixing IT problems since before virtualization was cool—30+ years and counting. These days
		I'm an infrastructure engineer at Pediatrix Medical Group, where I keep Nutanix clusters, Citrix
		environments, and Azure workloads running for healthcare teams who can't afford downtime.
	</p>

	<p>
		I'm a Nutanix Technology Champion with certifications across Nutanix (NCP-MCI, NCP-MCA), Citrix
		(CCP-V, CC-VAD-CC), Microsoft Azure, and CompTIA Security+. Most of my career has been in
		healthcare IT, where "the system is down" means something different than it does in most
		industries.
	</p>

	<p><strong>Why this blog?</strong></p>

	<p>
		Over the years I've solved a lot of problems that weren't well-documented anywhere:
		VMware-to-AHV migrations, Protection Domain-to-Policy conversions, Citrix upgrades that didn't go
		as planned. The kind of stuff that's hard to find in official docs because it only shows up when
		you're knee-deep in a change window at 2 AM.
	</p>

	<p>I write what I wish I could've Googled.</p>

	<p>Based in Georgia. Opinions are my own.</p>

